<p>Materials in this collection are stored offsite. For more information on making arrangements to consult them, please visit www.nyhistory.org/library/visit.</p><p>Open to qualified researchers with the exception of restricted materials. Restricted materials include contracts. Restricted materials are located in box R86.</p>  </accessrestrict>
  <arrangement id="aspace_5cfa5df57c8c46d178bd78f2ff378c9d">
    <head>Arrangement</head>
<p>The collection is arranged alphabetically based on the original arrangement.</p>  </arrangement>
  <bioghist id="aspace_14073797a1362f663b76173f0dd93fd8">
    <head>Historical Note</head>
<p>Selling Areas-Marketing, Inc. (SAMI) was founded by J. Clarke Mattimore, a consultant in the Time-Life Broadcast division, in 1965 to measure the sale of products by tracking inventory in wholesale warehouses. Reports produced from this information were offered for sale by subscription to consumer-goods manufacturing companies. Time Inc. Sold SAMI in 1987.</p><p>Citations:</p><p>Associated Press. "Time Will Sell SAMI-Burke to Control Data." Los Angeles Times, 14 Oct. 1987, www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-1987-10-14-fi-9248-story.html. </p><p>Prendergast, Curtis, and Geoffrey Colvin. 1986. <title render="italic">Time Inc.: The Intimate History of a Changing Enterprise, 1960-1980</title>. New York: Atheneum.</p>  </bioghist>
  <acqinfo id="aspace_006a7a31f9ec8cb2235ca2aea5b79109">
    <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
<p>Gift of Time Inc. in 2015.</p>  </acqinfo>
  <prefercite id="aspace_d97d30201e552db627d57355380c2b1d">
    <head>Preferred Citation</head>
